<h3>Targeting Struggling Buyers</h3>
</p>
        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="39.0">Exeter has always specialized in the subprime market. But in the late 2010s, the company went after customers with poor credit more aggressively than it had in the past. It accepted borrowers with even lower credit scores, lent them more money — as much as $50,000 per loan — and gave them longer to repay it. Some agreed to schedules stretching longer than six years, making the loans more costly.</p>
        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="40.0">“We’re not your father’s Exeter Finance,” the company proclaimed in a 2019 <a href="https://www.exeterfinance.com/blog/were-not-your-fathers-exeter-finance">blog post</a> aimed at wooing new business from dealerships.  </p>

<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="40.1">It also increased its prices.</p>
        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="41.0">ProPublica’s analysis shows that Exeter charges the highest interest rates of any lender in the publicly available data. Since 2020, the average interest rate for an Exeter car loan jumped from 19% to nearly 22%, regulatory records show.</p>
        
            
    
    
    
                            

<figure
    data-pp-id="1"
    data-pp-blocktype="embed"
    class="bb-embed size08 center  wide-sm wrap
                     bb--chunky-border-top                 hide-print
        ">

    
<div class="lead-in">
            <p class="lead-in__title" id="exeter-charged-higher-interest-rates-than-other-subprime-lenders">Exeter Charged Higher Interest Rates Than Other Subprime Lenders</p>
                <div class="lead-in__intro">
            <p>Rates for borrowers with the lowest credit scores were nearly 30%.</p>

        </div>
    </div>


                        <style>
	#g-credit-interest-20240506-box {
		max-width:750px;
margin: auto;
	}
	#g-credit-interest-20240506-box p {
		margin:0;
	}
	#g-credit-interest-20240506-box .g-aiAbs {
		position:absolute;
	}
	#g-credit-interest-20240506-box .g-aiImg {
		position:absolute;
		top:0;
		display:block;
