        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/why-title-lenders-excluded-chapter-13-bankruptcy-georgia">
                                    TitleMax Demands High-Interest Payments From Borrowers in Bankruptcy
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            In Georgia, borrowers looking to alleviate debt through Chapter 13 bankruptcy can’t escape their high-interest title pawns thanks to a legal loophole that TitleMax helped secure.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <span class="name">Margaret Coker</span>, <a href="https://thecurrentga.org">The Current</a>, and <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/joel-jacobs">Joel Jacobs</a> and <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/mollie-simon">Mollie Simon</a>, ProPublica, illustrations by <span class="name">Laila Milevski</span>, special to <a href="https://www.propublica.org">ProPublica</a>,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2023-07-13EDT05:00">July 13, 2023, 5 a.m. EDT</time>
